The paper deals with the problem of finding an optimal orthogonal drawing of a planar graph with varying edge costs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of cost functions and optimization also suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also mentions the concept of biconnected components, which is a topic in graph theory (cs.GT) and the running time analysis involves flow networks, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
